HEADWORD: Circumvest
<hw>Cir`cum*vest"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumvestire</ets>; <ets>circum + vestire</ets> to clothe.]</ety>
<def>To cover round, as with a garment; to invest.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Circumvested</qex> with much prejudice.</q> <rj><qau>Sir H.
Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumvolant</ent>⟦br⟧
